A basic metronome program

This is a simple metronome program for Linux.

It supports setting a tempo and a time signature. There's a simple
audio out using SDL, and an ability to play/pause the music by sending
DBus messages.  There is a simple curses interface.

Since audio is over sdl, pairing a bluetooth headset works trivially.

This is a simple yet very useful program.




I grew tired of Android-based metronome programs that weren't
convenient when viewing sheet music, as you have to switch between
apps, and they usually push ads in your face.

My desktop has a larger screen than any tablet I own, so this is more
convenient when practicing.